eStatus` (DRAFT, ACTIVE, ARCHIVED), `TicketStatus` (BACKLOG, READY, IN_PROGRESS, BLOCKED, DONE, CANCELED), `ScopeChangeCategory` (COMMIT_ADDED, COMMIT_REMOVED, ESTIMATE_CHANGED, CHESS_PIECE_CHANGED, RCDO_CHANGED, PRIORITY_CHANGED), `CarryForwardReason` enum with controlled list.\\n- Interfaces: `WeeklyPlan`, `Commit`, `RcdoNode`, `Ticket`, `LockSnapshot`, `ScopeChangeEvent`, `ReconcileSnapshot`, `CarryForwardLink`, `AiSuggestion`, `ManagerComment`, `CapacityOverride`, `Notification`.\\n- Constants: `VALID_ESTIMATE_POINTS = [1, 2, 3, 5, 8]`, `DEFAULT_WEEKLY_BUDGET = 10`, `MAX_KING_PER_WEEK = 1`, `MAX_QUEEN_PER_WEEK = 2`, `SOFT_MAX_COMMITS = 8`, `PAWN_POINT_WARNING_THRESHOLD = 0.4`.\\n- Validation helpers with unit tests (e.g., isValidEstimate, isChessPieceWithinLimit).\\n\\n**backend/ SQL migrations (Flyway):**\\nCreate Flyway migrations under `src/main/resources/db/migration/` for all transactional tables from PRD §23: organization, team, user_account, team_membership, weekly_plan, commit, lock_snapshot_header, lock_snapshot_commit, scope_change_event, reconcile_snapshot_header, reconcile_snapshot_commit, carry_forward_link, work_item, work_item_status_history, work_item_comment, rcdo_node, rcdo_change_log, manager_comment, capacity_override, notification, notification_delivery, ai_suggestion, ai_feedback, audit_log. Include proper indexes, foreign keys, unique constraints (e.g., one plan per user per week), and check constraints (e.g., valid estimate points).\\n\\n**backend/ Java entities:**\\nCreate JPA entity classes under a `domain` package mirroring each table. Use Java enums matching the TypeScript enums. Add Jakarta Bean Validation annotations. Create repository interfaces (Spring Data JPA). Write unit tests for entity validation.\",\n  \"requiredChecks\": [\n    \"lint\",\n    \"typecheck\",\n    \"unit\",\n    \"build\"\n  ]\n}\n\nYou are the first agent to work on this step.\nImplement the changes described above, run checks to verify, and fix any issues b